  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "Trim the scallions and separate them into individual rings.",
    "In a large bowl, whisk together sesame oil, minced garlic, grated ginger, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Add the scallion rings to the bowl and toss to coat with the garlic-ginger mixture.",
    "Transfer the scallion mixture to a baking dish and top with chopped green onions and crushed sesame seeds.",
    "Bake for 20 minutes or until the scallions are tender and slightly caramelized.",
    "Remove from the oven and drizzle with toasted sesame oil if using.",
    "Sprinkle with Korean chili flakes if desired.",
    "Serve warm and enjoy!"
  ],
